# Project Miyamoto → AI Personal Fitness Coach
## Refactor Plan — V7.0

### Background & Why

The current V6.2 app is a highly personalized martial-arts + strength tracker built for a single user (BG). It works, but it has several compounding issues:

- **Tight identity coupling** — BG's exact goals (BJJ, Muay Thai, handstand, Muay Thai sparring) are hard-coded into workout generators, domain names, and UI labels. Making it usable for anyone else means ripping out 40+ constants.
- **Accumulated complexity debt** — ~3,700 lines of spaghetti state: `migrateState()` patches on top of patches, reducer action types from 5 different rewrites, dead props (`currentMASubtype` living top-level next to `activeSession`), and fragile workout generators that mix business logic with UI code.
- **AI is an afterthought** — Gemini is a toggle in Settings, an optional API key, and fires one coaching note per-session. It's not the brain — it's a footnote. The app should be *led* by AI.
- **UX is dated** — Dark brutalist mono is cool but limits appeal and readability for a general audience.
- **No goal system** — The app assumes BG's goals. Real fitness coaching starts by asking what you want.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Complete rewrite, not incremental** — This plan proposes writing a new `miyamoto.html` from scratch (and a matching `.jsx`). The V6.2 code and localStorage key (`miyamoto_v5`) will be preserved during development. When the new V7.0 version is ready, it will use a new localStorage key (`miyamoto_v7`). Your old data can be exported from V6.2 before switching. A migration utility will be included in Settings.

> [!WARNING]
> **BG-specific hardcoding removed** — Domain names (striking, grappling), session types (martialArts), and skill trees (muscle-up, handstand) become *configurable* through onboarding. You'll still be able to configure the app to match your current exact setup — it just won't be hardcoded anymore.

> [!NOTE]
> **Same tech stack** — React + Tailwind + Recharts + Gemini API. Still a self-contained PWA HTML file. No new dependencies. Still works offline via service worker.

---

## Design Philosophy → V7.0

| Old (V6.2) | New (V7.0) |
|---|---|
| Dark brutalist mono | Premium dark-modern with system font stack |
| `font-mono` everywhere | Mono for data, sans for prose |
| Hard red accents only | Accent color chosen per user goal (red/blue/green/purple) |
| UPPERCASE labels | Sentence case with selective caps for emphasis |
| Sharp borders, no radius | Subtle radius (4-8px) for cards, sharp for CTAs |
| AI is optional footnote | AI is the primary coach interface |

---

## Proposed Changes

### Core Architecture

#### [MODIFY] miyamoto.html → V7.0 complete rewrite
#### [MODIFY] adaptive_training_platform.jsx → V7.0 complete rewrite

The files will be rewritten as a clean slate. The architecture remains the same pattern (single file, `useReducer`, Tailwind, Recharts, Gemini API) but with a completely restructured state shape and new UI.

---

### 1. Onboarding Redesign

**Current:** 2-step (name → age/bodyweight)

**New:** 5-step smart onboarding that configures the entire coaching engine:

| Step | What it collects |
|---|---|
| 1 — Who are you? | Name, age, biological sex, bodyweight |
| 2 — What's your goal? | Picker: Fat Loss / Muscle Gain / Strength / Endurance / Sport Performance / General Fitness |
| 3 — What do you train? | Multi-select: Gym (weights), Calisthenics, Running, Martial Arts, Cycling, Sport, Yoga/Mobility |
| 4 — How fit are you? | Quick self-assessment: Beginner / Intermediate / Advanced per selected discipline |
| 5 — Your schedule | Days/week + preferred session length |

From these 5 steps, the app **generates a personalized initial config** — session types, frequency targets, exercise selection filter, block periodization start point, and AI coaching persona.

---

### 2. New State Shape (V7.0)

```
profile          — name, age, sex, bodyweight, goal, disciplines[], fitnessLevels{}, 
                   daysPerWeek, sessionMinutes, accentColor
programConfig    — currentBlock, blockWeek, adaptationAggressiveness, coachPersona
athleteModel     — domainScores{}, fatigueDebt, consistencyScore, readinessTrend, streakDays
progression      — exercises{}, skills{}, stalledItems[], deloadRecommended, highRPEStreak
readiness        — inputs{sleep, stress, soreness, motivation, energyLevel}, score, band
muscleRecovery   — dynamic: generated from selected disciplines
aiConfig         — enabled, apiKey, model, endpoint
aiMemory         — coachingNotes[], weeklySummary, weeklyGoalCheck, lastSummaryAt
planState        — recommendation, secondaryRec, progressionPrompts[]
constraints      — injuries{}, blockedPatterns[], customSubstitutions{}
sessionLogs      — []
activeSession    — null | current session
```

Key changes:
- `disciplines[]` replaces hardcoded session types — everything derives from user's declared disciplines
- `aiMemory` replaces scattered `coachingNotes` and `weeklySummary` fields — AI has a proper memory object
- `accentColor` per-user theming
- `energyLevel` added to readiness (5th input, currently missing from V6.2)
- `customSubstitutions` — user can override any exercise substitution

---

### 3. AI Coach — The New Brain

The AI layer gets fundamentally upgraded from "notes on a card" to "the thing running the app."

#### 3a. AI Coach Chat Panel (NEW)
A persistent **chat interface** on the Home screen where the user can talk to their AI coach. The coach:
- Answers questions about today's training
- Explains why an exercise is being recommended
- Adjusts the day's plan based on what you tell it
- Remembers previous sessions via `aiMemory.coachingNotes[]`

The chat uses `callGeminiAPI()` with a rich system prompt that includes:
- User profile + goals
- This week's session history
- Today's readiness score
- Current progression state
- Last AI coaching note

#### 3b. Pre-Session Brief (NEW)
When the user starts a session, the AI generates a **3-bullet brief** before the workout begins:
- Today's training focus
- Key adaptation cue (e.g., "your quads are fresh — push leg volume")
- One coaching reminder (form, mindset, or pacing)

#### 3c. Post-Session Summary (IMPROVED)
The existing post-session coaching note gets more structure:
- Performance verdict (Advanced / Held / Regressed — and why)
- Top insight from this session
- What to focus on next session

#### 3d. Weekly Recap (IMPROVED from V6.2)
Existing `⚡ WEEKLY RECAP` card on Home is kept but given richer structure and a "Goal Progress" indicator showing proximity to the user's declared weekly goal.

---

### 4. Home Screen Redesign

**Current:** Profile summary → Session Balance → Recent logs → Readiness check

**New:**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ COACH GREETING (AI, personalized)   │
│ "Morning BG. Legs are fresh.        │
│  Today's optimal: Gym, 60 min"      │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│ TODAY'S RECOMMENDATION (big card)   │
│ [type] [time] [muscles fresh/tired] │
│ [START THIS SESSION] button         │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│ WEEKLY SNAPSHOT                     │
│ 3/6 sessions done · 65% goal       │
│ [streak badge] [recovery ring]      │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│ WEEKLY AI RECAP (when available)    │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│ QUICK READINESS CHECK (5 sliders)   │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

The "coach greeting" is statically generated from local state if AI is off, or calls Gemini if AI is on.

---

### 5. Training Session Flow (IMPROVED)

**Current:** Pick type → Workout → Complete → RPE modal → Done

**New:**

```
Pick type  →  AI Pre-Session Brief  →  Workout (unchanged core)  
   →  Per-exercise logging (unchanged)  →  RPE modal (+ energyLevel)  
   →  AI Post-Session Summary  →  Done
```

- The session picker now uses the **user's configured disciplines** instead of hardcoded types
- A new **Custom Session** option lets the user build a session manually

---

### 6. Progress View (IMPROVED)

- **Overview tab** — Body composition trend, weekly volume, consistency heatmap (GitHub-style)
- **Per-Domain tab** — Same sparklines as V6.2 but with projected trendlines
- **Skills tab** — Same calisthenics tree but now generalized to any skill progression the user defines during onboarding
- **Muscle Map tab** (NEW) — Visual body silhouette showing muscle fatigue status (color-coded fresh/recovering/fatigued) using inline SVG

---

### 7. Settings (EXPANDED)

New sections added:
- **Goal Recalibration** — Change primary goal without full reset
- **Discipline Manager** — Add/remove disciplines post-onboarding
- **AI Persona** — Choose coaching style (Drill Sergeant / Friendly Coach / Data Nerd / Silent)
- **Accent Color** — 6 presets
- **V6 Data Import** — Migrate from old `miyamoto_v5` localStorage key

---

### 8. Bug Fixes (from V6.2 — addressed in rewrite)

| Bug | Fix |
|---|---|
| `BackdropFilter` crash in transparent context | Removed — not used in new design system |
| Login/state race condition | N/A (no auth), but `migrateState()` race is resolved by clean initial state |
| Shimmer animation always running | New design uses CSS transitions, not always-on shimmer |
| Recharts `import` in Babel block (blank page) | Fixed in new clean file structure |
| Stale `weeklyKmResetAt` on import | Clean `migrateState()` with version guard |
| Dead props littering top-level state | Removed in new state shape |

